---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="For Families" description="Understanding trauma therapy - a guide for parents and caregivers supporting their child's treatment.">
  <section class="py-10 sm:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="max-w-3xl mb-12">
        <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl font-semibold text-charcoal mb-4">
          For Families
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed">
          Your child has started trauma therapy, and you want to understand what's happening and how you can help. These guides explain what happens in therapy without overwhelming jargon.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Available Now - Featured Section -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1 bg-coral-500 text-white text-sm font-medium rounded-full">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-white rounded-full animate-pulse"></span>
            Available Now
          </span>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <!-- EMDR Card -->
          <a
            href="/families/emdr"
            class="block group relative bg-gradient-to-br from-coral-500 to-coral-600 rounded-2xl p-6 text-white overflow-hidden hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1"
          >
            <!-- Background pattern -->
            <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10">
              <svg class="w-full h-full" viewBox="0 0 100 100" preserveAspectRatio="none">
                <defs>
                  <pattern id="grid-emdr" width="10" height="10" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
                    <path d="M 10 0 L 0 0 0 10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5"/>
                  </pattern>
                </defs>
                <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#grid-emdr)" />
              </svg>
            </div>

            <div class="relative">
              <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-white/20 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center backdrop-blur-sm mb-4">
                <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M15 12a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" />
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M2.458 12C3.732 7.943 7.523 5 12 5c4.478 0 8.268 2.943 9.542 7-1.274 4.057-5.064 7-9.542 7-4.477 0-8.268-2.943-9.542-7z" />
                </svg>
              </div>

              <h2 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold mb-2 group-hover:underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4">
                What is EMDR?
              </h2>
              <p class="text-white/85 text-sm mb-4">
                EMDR helps the brain process traumatic memories. Learn what your child experiences and how you can support them.
              </p>
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-2 py-0.5 bg-white/20 rounded-full text-xs backdrop-blur-sm">
                  <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
                  </svg>
                  Evidence-based
                </span>
                <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-2 py-0.5 bg-white/20 rounded-full text-xs backdrop-blur-sm">
                  <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
                  </svg>
                  Child-paced
                </span>
              </div>
              <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-medium text-white/90 group-hover:gap-2 transition-all">
                Learn more
                <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
                </svg>
              </div>
            </div>
          </a>

          <!-- Sand Tray Card -->
          <a
            href="/families/sandtray"
            class="block group relative bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-500 to-amber-600 rounded-2xl p-6 text-white overflow-hidden hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1"
          >
            <!-- Background pattern -->
            <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10">
              <svg class="w-full h-full" viewBox="0 0 100 100" preserveAspectRatio="none">
                <defs>
                  <pattern id="grid-sand" width="10" height="10" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
                    <path d="M 10 0 L 0 0 0 10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5"/>
                  </pattern>
                </defs>
                <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#grid-sand)" />
              </svg>
            </div>

            <div class="relative">
              <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-white/20 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center backdrop-blur-sm mb-4">
                <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M20 7l-8-4-8 4m16 0l-8 4m8-4v10l-8 4m0-10L4 7m8 4v10M4 7v10l8 4" />
                </svg>
              </div>

              <h2 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold mb-2 group-hover:underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4">
                What is Sand Tray Therapy?
              </h2>
              <p class="text-white/85 text-sm mb-4">
                Sand tray uses miniatures and creative play to help children express feelings without needing words.
              </p>
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-2 py-0.5 bg-white/20 rounded-full text-xs backdrop-blur-sm">
                  <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
                  </svg>
                  Creative
                </span>
                <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-2 py-0.5 bg-white/20 rounded-full text-xs backdrop-blur-sm">
                  <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
                  </svg>
                  Child-led
                </span>
              </div>
              <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-medium text-white/90 group-hover:gap-2 transition-all">
                Learn more
                <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
                </svg>
              </div>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Coming Soon Section -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1 bg-wood-200 text-wood-700 text-sm font-medium rounded-full">
            Coming Soon
          </span>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <!-- TF-CBT Card -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-wood-200 rounded-xl p-6 opacity-75">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-wood-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-wood-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M9.663 17h4.673M12 3v1m6.364 1.636l-.707.707M21 12h-1M4 12H3m3.343-5.657l-.707-.707m2.828 9.9a5 5 0 117.072 0l-.548.547A3.374 3.374 0 0014 18.469V19a2 2 0 11-4 0v-.531c0-.895-.356-1.754-.988-2.386l-.548-.547z" />
                </svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-charcoal mb-2">What is TF-CBT?</h3>
                <p class="text-charcoal/70 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
                  Trauma-Focused Cognitive Behavioral Therapy helps children and teens process trauma through structured activities and coping skills.
                </p>
                <span class="inline-block text-xs font-medium px-2 py-1 bg-wood-100 text-wood-600 rounded">
                  In Development
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- PCIT Card -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-wood-200 rounded-xl p-6 opacity-75">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-wood-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-wood-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" />
                </svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-charcoal mb-2">What is PCIT?</h3>
                <p class="text-charcoal/70 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
                  Parent-Child Interaction Therapy strengthens the parent-child bond and teaches effective parenting skills.
                </p>
                <span class="inline-block text-xs font-medium px-2 py-1 bg-wood-100 text-wood-600 rounded">
                  In Development
                </span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- How You Can Help Section -->
      <div class="bg-coral-50 rounded-xl p-8 max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-charcoal mb-4">
          How You Can Help
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-charcoal/80">
          <p>
            It's natural to have questions and concerns about your child's therapy. Learning about the treatment process can help you feel more confident and better equipped to support your child's healing journey.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm">
            <li>Be patient — healing takes time and isn't always linear</li>
            <li>Keep communication open without pushing</li>
            <li>Maintain routines and stability at home</li>
            <li>Ask the therapist how to support specific skills at home</li>
            <li>Take care of yourself too — your wellbeing matters</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-sm">
            The guides on this site are written in plain language by trauma therapists who work with families every day.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
